name: Phobias
description:
The purpose of phobias is to elicit a sense of realism, which is achieved by collecting DNA samples from various iconic models. These models are particularly effective when creating close-up portraits.

Caution: Phobias contain NSFW contents. Use with care.

The global illumination of the subject matter is a prominent characteristic of Phobias, which is then complemented by the texture and diversity of subjects.

Variation:

Fig.1. As observed, 'Phobias_c' still has problems with the eyelash.

Fig.2. The comparison between Phobias_b and Phobias_Pro
